Tokyo's stockmarket index plunged sharplyat the start of afternoon trade as investors took profits fromlast week's four straight record closes, brokers said.    The market index fell 427.48 points to 22,789.11 only 13minutes after afternoon trading began at 13:30 local time.    Brokers said concern over weekend announcements of mountingtrade tension with Europe and the U.S. Sparked the heavyselloff.    The average had risen 630.48 points in the last fourtrading sessions of last week. REUTER&#3;